reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Neat to look at and provides a home for gaming headset
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I ordered this for my son because in addition to looking fun with the colors, also helps him take better care of his gaming headset. He has a nice headset, and I am worried it is going to get broken. I often walk in his room, and it is still plugged into the computer but thrown on his bed, the computer chair, it was knocked on the floor. I have tripped on it a number of times. I am impressed it is still working.This stand gives it a home when he is not gaming and it lights up which is pretty neat. There are 10 different lighting settings from solid colors to multicolor to changing colors.I have to say, as an adult, I even got excited when I plugged it in and saw it light up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great looking, functional RGB headphone stand!
reviews.reviewText: I got the KANTUTOE RGB Gaming Headphone Stand Light for my teenage gamer daughter and she loves it! I am a big fan of RGB and so is my daughter so when she asked if I could get her an RGB headphone stand, I knew I needed to find her a good one.The light is bright without being too bright and the stand seems to be pretty sturdy. She likes that there are lights in the base as well as the pole and that it comes with a USB plug in the base is a nice bonus. She says it is the perfect size and doesn't take up too much desk space. That my teenage daughter loves the stand is a glowing endorsement (she is going to college soon for engineering so she looks at items like this as an engineer would) and means that I can definitely recommend the KANTUTOE RGB Gaming Headphone Stand Light!
